  <!-- Schools -->
  <section style="padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #3D5A3E; margin-bottom: 12px;">Alderley Edge schools</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What schools serve Alderley Edge families?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Alderley Edge Community Primary School is the village's only state primary, rated Good by Ofsted (December 2024) with Outstanding for behaviour and attitudes, personal development, and early years provision. The school admits approximately 203 pupils aged 4-11 from the village and surrounding area.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">At secondary level, Wilmslow High School (Ofsted Good) serves Alderley Edge, Wilmslow, and Handforth. The school is heavily oversubscribed and allocates places by distance from the school gates - not a fixed catchment boundary. Families buying at the eastern or southern edges of Alderley Edge face a higher risk of missing out on a place than those closer to Wilmslow.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Buyers with secondary-age children should verify their prospective address against the school's last published admission distance before committing to a purchase.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 24px 0;"><strong>Time-sensitive:</strong> Alderley Edge School for Girls (ISI Excellent, 2021) closes permanently on 7 July 2026. Families relocating after this date lose the village's only independent secondary option. The Ryleys School on Ryleys Lane continues to operate as an independent prep for ages 1-11. The <a href="/schools" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">Cheshire schools hub</a> covers county-wide options including <a href="/schools/best-primary-schools" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">best primary schools</a> and <a href="/schools/best-secondary-schools" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">best secondary schools</a>.</p>

      <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
        <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background-color: #F5F0E8;">
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8;">Alderley Edge school</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8;">Type</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8;">Rating</th>
              <th style="text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #1C1C1E; border-bottom: 2px solid #E5E0D8;">Note</th>
