  <!-- Safety -->
  <section style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #3D5A3E; margin-bottom: 12px;">Alderley Edge crime and safety</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Is Alderley Edge safe?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Alderley Edge's overall crime rate of 76.2 per 1,000 population requires context. The village centre's concentration of bars, restaurants, and late-night venues on London Road inflates the village-wide statistic. Residential postcodes within SK9 7 record approximately 30-31 crimes per 1,000 - described as "Low" by police.uk and well below the national average of 88.1 per 1,000 (ONS, 2024).</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">Cheshire Constabulary records the lowest crime rate in the North West at 69.8 offences per 1,000 people (year to March 2025). Within the Golden Triangle, Alderley Edge's residential rate sits below <a href="/where-to-live/wilmslow" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">Wilmslow</a>'s 51.4 per 1,000 when comparing like-for-like residential areas - though Wilmslow's overall figure is lower because the nightlife effect is diluted across a larger population.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lifestyle -->
  <section style="padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #3D5A3E; margin-bottom: 12px;">Alderley Edge lifestyle</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What defines daily life in Alderley Edge?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">London Road is Alderley Edge's social and commercial centre - a single walkable street where Victors, Alderley Bar and Grill, the Bubble Room, Piccolino, and YU Chinese draw diners from across the Golden Triangle. Coggles designer fashion store and independent retailers (cheese, meat, cakes) line the same stretch. The Wizard Restaurant on Macclesfield Road offers a dining option closer to The Edge escarpment.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">The Edge itself - a red sandstone escarpment managed by the National Trust since 1948 - rises directly above the village. Themed walks pass through pine and beech woodland to Stormy Point, Wizard's Well, and the remnants of copper mines dating to the Bronze Age. The highest point served as both a burial mound and a fire beacon in antiquity.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Alderley Edge is the only Golden Triangle village where National Trust countryside sits within a five-minute walk of the dining scene - a proximity that directly sustains the village's price premium over Wilmslow and Prestbury.</p>

      <h3 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; margin: 32px 0 12px 0;">What heritage shapes Alderley Edge's identity?</h3>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Alderley Edge hosts the oldest known metal-mining site in England (Derbyshire Caving Club/National Trust archaeological survey). Stone hammers and mauls recovered from the escarpment date to the Bronze Age, and an oak shovel found in the 1870s was carbon-dated to approximately 1750 BC. A Roman mineshaft with a 4th-century AD coin pot confirms continuous extraction spanning over 4,000 years.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">The Wizard legend - a 19th-century tale of a sleeping army guarded beneath The Edge - inspired Alan Garner's 1960 novel The Weirdstone of Brisingamen. The legend permeates village naming: the Wizard pub, the Wizard Restaurant, and Wizard's Well on the escarpment trail.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">The Pilkington family donated the escarpment woodland to the National Trust in 1948, establishing the conservation framework that now constrains residential development on the village's western boundary and sustains the Green Belt designation protecting Alderley Edge's setting.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Employment -->
  <section style="background-color: #FFFFFF; border-top: 1px solid #E5E0D8; border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E0D8; padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #3D5A3E; margin-bottom: 12px;">Alderley Edge employment</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">Where do Alderley Edge residents work?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Alderley Edge residents predominantly commute to Manchester city centre for professional services, media, and finance roles. A 27-minute Northern Trains journey from Alderley Edge station to Manchester Piccadilly makes the village a practical base for daily commuters. Manchester Airport (8 miles, 15-20 minutes by car) employs 25,000+ across all operators and is accessible via the M56.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Alderley Park - a 400-acre life science campus in neighbouring Nether Alderley - provides a local employment alternative that no other Golden Triangle village can match. The former AstraZeneca site (departed 2014) is now operated by Bruntwood SciTech and hosts over 200 businesses across 1 million+ square feet of laboratory and office space. Key tenants include the Medicines Discovery Catapult (government-funded drug discovery accelerator), the Cancer Research UK Manchester Institute, and the AMR Centre for antimicrobial resistance research.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0;">Researchers, scientists, and pharma professionals relocating to Alderley Park typically settle in Alderley Edge - the nearest village to the campus at under 2 miles. Alderley Park occupies a comparable role for life science recruitment that <a href="/where-to-live/knutsford" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">Knutsford</a>'s Barclays Radbroke Hall fills for banking professionals.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Buying Practicalities -->
  <section style="padding: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px) 24px;">
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #C4933F; margin-bottom: 12px;">Alderley Edge buyer checklist</span>
      <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; color: #1C1C1E; line-height: 1.25; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">What should buyers check before purchasing in Alderley Edge?</h2>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">Alderley Edge sits within the Cheshire salt field, where historical brine extraction caused ground movement across the Cheshire Plain. Solicitors conducting <a href="/buying-guide/conveyancing-cheshire" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">conveyancing on Cheshire properties</a> commission a salt search (approximately £30-£50) to confirm whether the plot falls within a Cheshire Brine Subsidence Compensation Board claim area. Most Alderley Edge residential properties pass without issues, but the search is standard practice for SK9 transactions.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 16px 0;">The village centre sits within a conservation area, restricting external modifications to properties - replacement windows, extensions, and demolitions require additional planning consent from Cheshire East Council. Buyers of period properties in the conservation area should factor in these restrictions when assessing renovation potential.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; color: #444444; margin: 0 0 24px 0;">At Alderley Edge price levels, <a href="/buying-guide/stamp-duty-cheshire" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">stamp duty</a> represents a significant upfront cost. A property at the £750,000 average incurs approximately £27,500 in SDLT for a primary residence (2025-26 rates). Buyers purchasing a second home or buy-to-let face a 5% surcharge on top of standard rates. The <a href="/buying-guide/survey-types-cheshire" style="color: #3D5A3E; text-decoration: underline;">survey types guide</a> covers the appropriate survey level for Alderley Edge's predominantly period housing stock.</p>
      <p style="font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; color: #999999; margin: 0;"><strong style="color: #888888;">Sources:</strong> Property prices from <a href="https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/Alderley-Edge.html" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" style="color: #999999;">Rightmove</a> and <a href="https://www.zoopla.co.uk/house-prices/alderley-edge/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" style="color: #999999;">Zoopla</a> (last 12 months to 2025). Price per sqm from <a href="https://www.housemetric.co.uk/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" style="color: #999999;">HouseMetric</a>. Crime data from <a href="https://www.police.uk/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" style="color: #999999;">police.uk</a> and Cheshire Constabulary (year to March 2025). School ratings from <a href="https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" style="color: #999999;">Ofsted</a>. Train times from <a href="https://www.nationalrail.co.uk/" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" style="color: #999999;">National Rail</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

